        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-30 16:31:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nIt's better than crashing, but I wonder about the overhead of initializing a new env for every RPC if NRS ORR is enabled. Is it not possible to fix the caller to have its own env in this case?\n\nNikitas, this kind of bug means to me that we do not have any test case that runs even basic NRS testing of policies. Can you please submit a test that is enabling each if the NRS policies in turn and submitting some IO. Maybe sanityn.sh so that it can do something sensible for all the policies. Nothing too huge (e.g. dd a couple of MB each to two files per mountpoint, then a couple MB each for two threads per mountpoint to the same file with disjoint offsets).  Just enough to ensure the code is working at a basic level.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
